Summary: Running ./manage.py dumpdata dumps the the JSONField as a Python dictionary string instead of a JSON string.

e.g.

```json
[
    {
        "model": "myapp.mymodel",
        "pk": 1,
        "fields": {
            "my_json_field": "{'field1': None, 'field2': False}"
        }
    }
]
```

instead of 

```json
[
    {
        "model": "myapp.mymodel",
        "pk": 1,
        "fields": {
            "my_json_field": "{\"field1\": null, \"field2\": false}"
        }
    }
]
```

*If this is a bug, please fill in the below, else delete*

Django Version: Django 1.10.6

Database and version used: MySQL 5.7

Version: Django-MySQL 1.1.1

